6:
Wh-whoa, this is incredible! They set
up a whole racetrack!
10:
Indeed. I'd heard they were testing
out the mobility of new golems, but I
fail to understand why they installed
audience seating...
15:
Well, you see... Some teachers from
Voluntas got into a big argument
about whose golems were the
fastest.
19:
At which point the Guild figured...
why not make a whole festival out of
it? And here we are!
23:
I see... I shouldn't have expected any
less from the enterprising
merchants of Palpebra. You've
made quite the event out of this!
33:
On the day of the actual race, the
place will be filled to the brim with
food stalls! I hope you'll consider
dropping by—
40:
A shift! Is something happening in
the Kaleidoscope?!
48:
Ouch, that hurt! What's going on,
that wall just appeared out of
nowhere!
55:
Weren't we just in the equipment
room a second ago? Was there a
secret door I missed or something?!
59:
Who knows... Tracen Academy's got
its quirks, but this is something else
entirely.
62: This place really is beautiful, though.
67:
You're right, Suzuka. We're definitely
not in Tracen Academy anymore.
86: G-Gold Ship? Where are you going?!
90:
Woo-hoo! The biggest discovery of
the century is calling out to me, I
can hear it!
97:
...Um. Are you really sure it's safe to
just keep running ahead like this?
101:
I'm also unsure... But I must say, this
place has piqued my interest.
107: N-no way, not you too, Suzuka!
111:
More outsiders? Gah, they never
cease pestering me...
115:
I've had more than enough of
cleaning up after their messes! I'll
have to get rid of them as quickly as—
124:
W-wait... That was another person
back there, wasn't it?!
128:
We don't have time to talk to NPCs.
Golshi Any% Speed Run, coming
through!
133:
Judging by the scale of the last shift,
something strange definitely
happened in the Kaleidoscope. The
question is what.
136:
The two of you should stay on
guard, you never know what could
come flying out—
142:
Wh-what was that just now? That
speed... Were those humans?!
146:
Human or no, they're almost
certainly drifters... Probably came in
off of that last shift.
162:
I've never seen a course like this
before...
167:
But... Since we're here, it can't hurt to
have a little race, can it?
187:
Phew. Worked up a good sweat
there.
191:
Do you really think it was okay to just
use this racetrack without
permission?
196:
*pant*
Oh thank goodness... You finally...
stopped running...
200: Alk... Just who are these ladies?
207:
A-anyway... Could we have a
moment of your time?
213:
I see... So you call yourselves
"Umamusume", and you possess
extraordinary running abilities...
217:
That's right! Wait... is this your first
time ever seeing an Umamusume in
person?
220:
Actually, I was the only one in my
hometown too! I never met another
Umamusume until I went to Tracen
Academy.
225:
I think you might be
misunderstanding the situation...
230:
Spe, I think these people have never
even heard of an Umamusume
before.
235:
Wait, what? How is that possible?
The Twinkle Series is on TV every
single week!
247:
Please do not be alarmed by what
I'm about to say. You currently find
yourselves very far from home.
251:
What he means to say is...
You're in another world.
